<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/1550:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Istanbul</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Berry</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-31">July 31,
                                    1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>275R67. On good authority I am informed that just before leaving
                                Turkey for Italy Guariglia, the new Italian Foreign Minister, told
                                Vörnle, the Hungarian Minister to Turkey, that he expected to make
                                peace soon, if terms beneficial to Italy, within the framework of
                                the Allied unconditional surrender demand.</p>
                            <p>Guariglia asked Vörnle if his government wanted him to include
                                Hungary in the peace negotiations. Vörnle cabled his conversation to
                                Budapest and ask[ed] that a [reply be?<note n="1" xml:id="d243fn1">Garbled as received.</note>] transmitted to Rome.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berry</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>